The paper proposes a consensus algorithm for deep neural networks that improves interpretability and handles adversarial examples and out-of-distribution samples. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
